kairos — CLAP container runtime for cljseq-generated plugins
Copyright (C) 2026 Thomas Rodgers and contributors

This project uses a dual-license structure:

  LGPL-2.1-or-later  — public headers and library sources (include/, src/
                        excluding src/main.cpp and any translation units that
                        directly link Ableton Link)

  GPL-2.0-or-later   — the kairos executable binary, which embeds the Ableton
                        Link reference implementation (GPL-2.0-or-later)

The LGPL-2.1-or-later license grants a linking exemption: C++ code that
includes kairos headers or links against kairos-core as a shared library is
not subject to the GPL requirement, provided modifications to kairos-core
itself are shared under LGPL-2.1-or-later.

The kairos runtime binary as distributed (statically linking Ableton Link) is
subject to GPL-2.0-or-later in its entirety.

Full license texts:
  LICENSES/LGPL-2.1-or-later.txt
  LICENSES/GPL-2.0-or-later.txt

SPDX identifiers on each source file indicate which license applies.
